cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of neural networks for automatic interpretation of seismic images. This involves image segmentation, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a loss function and labeling strategies to train the neural network, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of a multi-resolution network and the consideration of small and large-scale geological features are also relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for automatic interpretation, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
